I'm looking to design a replacement battery bay for a mini quadcopter, specifically the X-shape ones like the one from xheli.com (http://www.xheli.com/28h-u207-quad-light.html). The idea is to ditch the existing plastic upper cover and integrate the battery holder directly, which will lighten the overall weight. I've already got an idea of the basic shape, and a rough, non-parametric OpenSCAD file. I'd like a fully parametric version of that design.

Here's the current design, which I've written out as a non-parametric SCAD file:

```
union() {
  difference() {
    cube([22, 24, 10], center=true);
    // cube([21, 24, 9], center=true);
    cube([18, 26, 8], center=true);
    translate([0, -5.5, 0]) {
      cube([24, 9, 6], center=true);
    }
    translate([0, 5.5, 0]) {
      cube([24, 9, 6], center=true);
    }
    translate([0, -5.5, 0]) {
      cube([16, 9, 12], center=true);
    }
    translate([0, 5.5, 0]) {
      cube([16, 9, 12], center=true);
    }
  }

  translate([0, 0, -6.5]) {
    difference() {
      cube([22, 11, 5], center=true);
      cube([19, 13, 1.75], center=true);
      cube([16, 13, 6], center=true);
      cube([24, 7, 6], center=true);
    }
  }
}
```

So, what I'm looking for is a parametric version. I'd like to be able to adjust the outer dimensions of the box (length, width, height), the width and depth of the internal cutout that's meant to hold the battery, and the depth of the inset on the bottom.  I also need all of the intermediate dimensions (like the inner dimensions of the main cutout) to be generated automatically based on the parameters that have been set (so for example, if the main cutout is 18x26, the dimensions of the inner cutouts on the sides should be a little bit smaller than that). Basically, everything should scale in a sensible way when the base parameters are changed.

I think it would also be useful to add a parameter for the wall thickness, that way we can change how strong the part is by changing a single number.

Also, I'd prefer if all the code was in a single file if that's possible, and that the file uses the BOSL2 library for things like `roundedcube()`.

```scad
union() {
  difference() {
    cube([22, 24, 10], center=true);

    cube([18, 26, 8], center=true);
    translate([0, -5.5, 0]) {
      cube([24, 9, 6], center=true);
    }
    translate([0, 5.5, 0]) {
      cube([24, 9, 6], center=true);
    }
    translate([0, -5.5, 0]) {
      cube([16, 9, 12], center=true);
    }
    translate([0, 5.5, 0]) {
      cube([16, 9, 12], center=true);
    }
  }

  translate([0, 0, -6.5]) {
    difference() {
      cube([22, 11, 5], center=true);
      cube([19, 13, 1.75], center=true);
      cube([16, 13, 6], center=true);
      cube([24, 7, 6], center=true);
    }
  }
}
```

