- Trig functions (sin, cos, tan) take RADIANS in ImplicitCAD, NOT degrees.
  Always use the degree-safe wrappers defined at the top of every file:
    deg2rad = 3.14159265358979 / 180;
    function sind(x) = sin(x * deg2rad);
    function cosd(x) = cos(x * deg2rad);
    function tand(x) = tan(x * deg2rad);
    function asind(x) = asin(x) / deg2rad;
    function acosd(x) = acos(x) / deg2rad;
    function atand(x) = atan(x) / deg2rad;
    function atan2d(y, x) = atan2(y, x) / deg2rad;
  Use sind(), cosd(), tand() etc. everywhere — never bare sin()/cos().
- Use explicit union() when combining multiple top-level objects.
